//Medial meniscus degeneration - Localization (multiple selection)


Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 05 - Ligaments, joint capsule & menisci of Knee MRI
When I select the radio button 'Finding'
Then 'Finding' dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'Medial meniscus degeneration' from the Finding dropdown
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And multiple selection Localizer is enabled
And 'Classification' grades are enabled

And 'Chondropathy' checkbox is enabled
And 'Bone marrow edema, subchondral' checkbox is enabled
And 'Subchondral sclerosis' checkbox is enabled
And 'Meniscus extrusion/subluxation' checkbox is enabled
And 'Degenerative posterior root tear' checkbox is enabled
And 'Meniscal cyst' checkbox is enabled
And 'Meniscocapsular separation' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'IMVH' part on the Localizer
Then 'IMVH' part is selected and turns red
When I select 'IMPI' part on the Localizer
Then 'IMPI' part is selected and turns red
When I select 'IMHH' part on the Localizer
Then 'IMHH' part is selected and turns red
